  "name": "Living Legend",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/control/control-influence-crown-yellow.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 20th level, you can empower yourself with the legends — whether true or exaggerated — of your great deeds. As a bonus action, you gain the following benefits for 1 minute:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You are blessed with an otherworldly presence, gaining <strong>advantage </strong>on all Charisma checks.</li>\n<li>Once on each of your turns when you make a weapon attack and miss, you can cause that attack to hit instead.</li>\n<li>If you fail a <strong>saving throw</strong>, you can use your reaction to reroll it. You must use this new roll.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you use this feature, you can’t use it again until you finish a <strong>long rest</strong>, unless you expend a <strong>5th-level spell slot</strong> to use it again.</p>",
